<br>
If you want good exp at 9 go to West Commons and solo Young Kodiaks with Fire elemental and kill the occasional black bear you might find a HQ(HQbear pelts go for 40pp on Cazic-thule) although HQ pelts are not found on YK's the exp is around 1/4 bubble, also kill willow wisps in hopes of finding a greater lightstone, you can turn in somewhere in RO and get good exp that way. Just remember med up you don't want to get jumped with no mana. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwudanicecruncher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wudan Icecruncher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(9/7/00 12:46:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LVL 8-11 where to hunt</span><hr size=1> While I am a Barbarian Shaman the information will be much the same.  Get one or two friends, one a healer type, and go to Erud's Crossing and hunt Wisps there, be very careful, at your level and to level 11, pull them one at a time to the beach and then kill them and share the loot.<br>
<br>
My Warrior, Trebert of Cazic-Thule Server, has hunted there with a Druid friend since he was 11, Druid was 9, yesterday, he came away with over 60pp for about 4 hrs play and 4 bubble of exp.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uommundanrii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ommundan Rii</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/x.bmp BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Hunt</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(9/8/00 12:53:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/SUMMON.BMP WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: things to kill!....at level 9 and a half?</span><hr size=1> I have simply one thing to say (in the qeynos area):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BANDITS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
According to<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/zone.php3?tag=qey2hh1">www.eqmaps.com/zone.php3?tag=qey2hh1</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
they range in level from 9-10.<br>
<br>
With a druid and harmony, the camps should be no problem.<br>
<br>
Two things to lookout for:<br>
<br>
1. Caster bandits. They cast as druids, have a damage shield and Ignite and Whirling wind the heck out of you. My wife's 19th lvl warrior has troubles taking on two of these.<br>
<br>
2. Brigands. They are lvl 15 and can take off two bubs of life off the wife's warrior.<br>
<br>
Check out this info sheet:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/infosheet.php3?tag=qey2hh1">www.eqmaps.com/infosheet....ag=qey2hh1</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You want to make you way to the &quot;Bandit Farm&quot;. There are two &quot;A Farmer&quot;s there that are really Bandits (you'll know by how they con). The female &quot;a farmer&quot;s almost always drop a bandit sash. (If you come here on Rodcet, I'll probably be there) If you have a large group, you can pull from the nearby mountain camp too.<br>
<br>
The sashes are the reason for being there. They are light weight and you turn them in in Qeynos. When you turn one in the guy gives you a bronze weapon that can sell from 1-2.5pp (maybe more if you make a human enchanter mule with a high charisma). I made 100pp with the wife's warrior the other night while playing her on the side for a couple hours. i even managed to get almost a bubble of exp from turning them in. Not to mention that between killing the bandits and turning in sashes, all of qeynos loves her <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I can't link to alakazam's web site from here at work, but I'll edit it in from home <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The guy's name is Chessgard something, and he is in the house of thunder in south Qeynos. Go to the far (south) dock and turn left. Pass fishes ale, then take a right, go through an arch in the wall and you're there.<br>
<br>
Black Burrow is also not too bad a place to go in a group (too many trains to make survival easy when you're solo), and I took my shaman from 8th to 9th on the giant snakes in there (it's really cool, you can stay on the wall slightly down off the main path in the room with like 5 snake spawns, and gnolls going to and from trains will not mess with you). After that I took her back out into everfrost and soloed yellow kitties and spiders and orcs (yellow to a 9th lvl). They give good exp up to like 12th when you can start on the weaker calfs with 2 or 3 people groups (watch out for mama's though). This was all with a shaman, so I know a Magi could handle it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Okay, this got rather long winded (no way! me? long winded?) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
If I had it to do over, I would have tried to group with a druid at the bandits since there is sooo much plat to be made there.<br>
<br>
The gnoll fang/blackburrow stout quest is cool too (BOOZE!!!) but Black Burrow is so poorly pathed and trained so often since the mobs are so mixed in level it's hard to not run into stuff that agros on you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Both places give good faction hits so Q-town will love you either way. Black Burrow adds faction with Surefall glade's druids (but not the wandering guards, go figure) so it's usefull for quests out of there. The bandits make all of the good guys in the Karanas like you.<br>
<br>
Hope all this rambling of mine helps someone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p><b>Ommundan Rii</b><br>
<img src="http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/LLRINGS.GIF"><br>
