<br>
Two ways (one is theoreticaly)<br>
<br>
As an enchanter you use a combo of illusions and &quot;make people like me&quot; spells (Illu. Orge or Dark Elf, and Benevolence or Alliance).<br>
<br>
The trouble being to get the book to take to Oggok you have to be a good race (or spend days or real time working on faction) to get Erud's Tonic. The Kiolandi fish, you could kill Frostbite over and over until you get one. thye Honey Jum is only lore, so a halfling mule or a friend could do it (same for the Kiola nut). But! to turn all the crap in you have to go into an East freeport bar that is either full of neutral thieves (that might leave an ogre alone I'm not sure there) bards and sometimes warriors of the Steel Warrior faction and merchants. Most of them will beat the poop out of evils <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As an evil, raising all that faction would be sooo hard. As a good race, it's not that hard to raise Oggok faction killing frogs, but the bartender Clerg has his own special faction that you can only raise by doing the stein quest.<br>
<br>
That's why it's an only enchanters quest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Take care, <p><b>Ommundan Rii</b><br>
